## What

Remove the Phase 0 busy-loop from TcpListener and use proper reactor-based accept().

## Location

`src/net/tcp/listener.rs`

## Current Implementation (Phase 0)

```rust
pub async fn accept(&self) -> io::Result<(TcpStream, SocketAddr)> {
    loop {
        match self.inner.accept() {
            Ok((stream, addr)) => {
                stream.set_nonblocking(true)?;
                return Ok((TcpStream::from_std(stream), addr));
            }
            Err(ref e) if e.kind() == io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock => {
                crate::runtime::yield_now().await;  // Phase 0: polite busy-loop
            }
            Err(e) => return Err(e),
        }
    }
}
```

## New Implementation (Phase 2)

```rust
pub struct TcpListener {
    inner: net::TcpListener,
    registration: Option<Registration>,
}

impl TcpListener {
    pub async fn bind<A: ToSocketAddrs>(addr: A) -> io::Result<Self> {
        let inner = net::TcpListener::bind(addr)?;
        inner.set_nonblocking(true)?;

        // Register with reactor for READABLE (incoming connections)
        let cx = Cx::current();
        let registration = cx.register_io(
            &TcpListenerSource(&inner),
            Interest::READABLE,
        )?;

        Ok(Self {
            inner,
            registration: Some(registration),
        })
    }

    pub async fn accept(&self) -> io::Result<(TcpStream, SocketAddr)> {
        poll_fn(|cx| self.poll_accept(cx)).await
    }

    pub fn poll_accept(&self, cx: &mut Context<'_>) -> Poll<io::Result<(TcpStream, SocketAddr)>> {
        match self.inner.accept() {
            Ok((stream, addr)) => {
                stream.set_nonblocking(true)?;

                // Create TcpStream with its own registration
                let cx_runtime = Cx::current();
                let registration = cx_runtime.register_io(
                    &TcpStreamSource(&stream),
                    Interest::READABLE | Interest::WRITABLE,
                )?;

                let tcp_stream = TcpStream {
                    inner: stream,
                    registration: Some(registration),
                };

                Poll::Ready(Ok((tcp_stream, addr)))
            }
            Err(ref e) if e.kind() == io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock => {
                // No pending connection, reactor will wake when one arrives
                Poll::Pending
            }
            Err(e) => Poll::Ready(Err(e)),
        }
    }
}
```

## Accept Loop Pattern

Common server pattern:
```rust
let listener = TcpListener::bind("127.0.0.1:8080").await?;

loop {
    let (stream, addr) = listener.accept().await?;

    // Spawn task to handle connection
    cx.spawn(async move {
        handle_connection(stream).await;
    });
}
```

## Registering Accepted Sockets

Each accepted socket gets its own Registration:
1. Listener is registered for READABLE
2. Accepted stream is registered for READABLE | WRITABLE
3. Each registration has unique token

## Cancel-Safety

If accept() is cancelled:
- poll_fn dropped, no side effects
- Listener registration still active
- Next accept() will work normally

